WEBVTT

00:00.290 --> 00:01.894
Hey, connection's church, Mark Clark here.

00:01.934 --> 00:03.016
Hopefully you were doing well.

00:03.057 --> 00:08.028
This is the last of the four week series that we are doing in the Psalms.

00:08.730 --> 00:11.597
And it has been awesome as we've journeyed through the first three weeks.

00:11.637 --> 00:17.170
And so this is week four and we're talking about Psalm chapter 27.

00:17.250 --> 00:34.607
And so remember we were choosing kind of four Psalms in the first 41 chapters, which are considered book one of the Psalms, to go, hey, what does it actually look like to connect to God through this kind of the songs and the arts and the prayers and stuff that is soul stuff.

00:34.687 --> 00:37.012
And that's a beautiful part of what this Psalm is.

00:37.052 --> 00:38.034
This is one of the best Psalms.

00:38.530 --> 00:41.175
because it really connects to what we're longing for.

00:41.235 --> 00:44.561
So how many of you asked the question, you know, how do I find joy?

00:44.581 --> 00:45.543
How do I find beauty?

00:45.563 --> 00:48.488
How do I find fulfillment and flourish in life?

00:48.949 --> 00:51.814
And this psalm actually talks about all of the ways to do that.

00:51.894 --> 00:54.439
Contentment, what's the dream of your life?

00:54.459 --> 00:56.322
What are you ultimately pining for?

00:56.443 --> 00:58.046
And this whole psalm talks about it.

00:58.066 --> 01:00.490
And I'm not going to get to all the verses because it's a beautiful Psalm.

01:00.510 --> 01:01.512
You should go home and read the whole thing.

01:02.013 --> 01:02.674
Verse one.

01:03.170 --> 01:07.910
says this, and I'm going to hone in on a lot of these concepts during our time together today.

01:08.031 --> 01:10.642
The Lord, meaning life starts.

01:10.722 --> 01:29.178
with God, so 27 verse one, the Lord, that's what the whole Psalm starts with, the Lord meaning God is supposed to be the center of all things in your life, which is beautiful and good, because that means you aren't, which is a really good thing, because it helps you when you're sitting in traffic and you're like, I don't, why am I in traffic?

01:29.198 --> 01:34.022
It's like, because the universe is not about you, or when you're fighting in your marriage, why am I fighting in my marriage?

01:34.042 --> 01:35.203
Why does my marriage feel like it stinks?

01:35.223 --> 01:40.708
Well, because the universe isn't about you, it's ultimately about God, and through the great times, and through the difficult times,

01:40.688 --> 01:44.293
supposed to be able to find your soul in God, not yourself.

01:44.333 --> 01:46.696
And so those of you who are exploring Christianity, we're glad you're here.

01:47.196 --> 01:52.864
You gotta find it in Jesus, not yourself, not in your circumstances, not in your beauty, not in your money.

01:52.964 --> 01:54.826
And this is what we've been talking about through the whole series.

01:55.127 --> 02:02.796
It's this concept that Paul talks about in Philippians 4 that I have, I've been in situations where I had no money and I've been content.

02:02.837 --> 02:08.263
And I've been in situations where I have a lot of money and I've been content because my contentment doesn't come through rich as it comes through Christ.

02:08.284 --> 02:10.226
It's Paul's whole point in Philippians 4.

02:10.690 --> 02:18.051
Now he says, and this is great because people criticize you at work, or whatever your situation is in life, your whole identity is now in the Lord.

02:18.071 --> 02:18.954
That's what he's talking about, the Lord.

02:18.994 --> 02:21.721
And then he says, is my light, underline that word light.

02:22.323 --> 02:23.346
This is beautiful because

02:23.874 --> 02:29.699
This is the only place in the Old Testament that God is called light, which is fascinating.

02:29.739 --> 02:31.841
He's called light in the New Testament a bunch.

02:31.861 --> 02:38.967
John chapter one, he says, in Christ was life and that life was the light of all mankind.

02:39.067 --> 02:42.170
The light shines in the darkness and the darkness does not overcome it.

02:42.230 --> 02:44.852
And so there's this sense of God being light.

02:44.912 --> 02:46.814
And the image of light, this is really important for your life.

02:46.894 --> 02:48.035
It's like revelation.

02:48.075 --> 02:51.558
It's like your life is dark and muddy and messy and confusing.

02:51.598 --> 02:53.860
And the life that you're living, you're trying to make money

02:53.840 --> 02:57.304
and keep them relationship together or date or whatever your situation is in life.

02:58.105 --> 02:59.748
And you need light.

02:59.968 --> 03:01.169
You need revelation.

03:01.229 --> 03:07.878
It's not good to walk through life without being clarity, having clarity of mind and heart on what is going on.

03:08.138 --> 03:09.620
On the question of salvation, we'll forget that.

03:09.640 --> 03:11.723
On the question of God and the question of your own soul.

03:12.083 --> 03:14.166
On the question of where do you find fulfillment in life?

03:14.186 --> 03:16.769
And so what he's saying is, is God is light.

03:17.010 --> 03:18.672
He brings revelation.

03:18.732 --> 03:19.753
He shows you stuff.

03:19.793 --> 03:20.674
He teaches you stuff.

03:20.694 --> 03:21.696
He speaks to you.

03:21.736 --> 03:23.538
It's beautiful through the Bible.

03:23.586 --> 03:29.289
through the impression of the Holy Spirit, through people, through preachers and teachers and leaders and other people around you.

03:29.771 --> 03:32.402
He still speaks, which is amazing.

03:32.482 --> 03:37.591
A couple of weeks ago, I was asked to go and speak up at a church in Reno, Nevada.

03:38.052 --> 03:41.317
And I went up there and it was this men's conference and they said, we want you to talk to our men.

03:41.919 --> 03:44.022
And I was up there and I was preaching a passage, guys.

03:44.082 --> 03:48.951
Honestly, I'd preached this passage a hundred times in my life out of Matthew chapter 16.

03:48.991 --> 03:53.619
And I'm kind of preaching it to them and I get to this part where Jesus looks at the disciples and Peter and says, who do people say that I am?

03:53.940 --> 03:57.586
And Peter says, you are the Messiah, son of the living God.

03:58.114 --> 04:02.401
And Jesus looks at Peter and he says this, blessed are you Simon son of Jonah.

04:02.421 --> 04:08.931
This is Matthew 16 verse 17, for this was not revealed to you by flesh and blood, but by my father in heaven.

04:09.012 --> 04:17.425
And I'd never, I'd preach this sermon a hundred times, I'd done it at men's conferences and kind of do this rallying cry about our dads and all this kind of stuff.

04:17.505 --> 04:20.069
And the brokenness that comes from dads that were failed and all of this.

04:20.190 --> 04:22.994
And on the spot, well, I'm on the stage, this is two weeks ago.

04:23.330 --> 04:26.113
The Holy Spirit literally teaches something to me on the spot.

04:26.473 --> 04:28.935
And I'm up there and I'm like, oh my gosh, guys, I just realized something.

04:29.175 --> 04:31.678
Literally on the spot right now, I just realized something.

04:31.698 --> 04:32.679
And I said, see what Jesus says?

04:32.979 --> 04:37.563
Blessed are you Simon, son of Jonah, meaning your dad's name is Jonah, all right?

04:38.024 --> 04:43.369
And I know him and I made him in his womb and I know all the way he grew up and I know his parents and all the rest.

04:43.409 --> 04:46.231
But Simon, Peter, your dad's name is Jonah.

04:47.052 --> 04:48.474
And he's a good dad and he's great, whatever.

04:49.014 --> 04:53.298
But he says, my father in heaven revealed this to you.

04:53.474 --> 04:57.380
And in that moment, I realized that Jesus was comparing daddies.

04:58.302 --> 05:03.590
All right, he's doing what we did in the courtyard as little kids at school, right?

05:03.610 --> 05:04.932
My daddy can beat up your daddy.

05:04.972 --> 05:06.335
My daddy's smarter than your daddy.

05:06.375 --> 05:08.598
My daddy's got a hotter wife than your daddy.

05:08.618 --> 05:08.959
That's weird.

05:08.979 --> 05:15.409
But this whole concept of daddies, and he's going, man, I know you had a dad, an earthly dad.

05:15.429 --> 05:17.432
And some of you are out there, you had a bad earthly dad.

05:17.452 --> 05:18.654
Some of you had a great earthly dad.

05:19.055 --> 05:20.978
And he's going, you know what ultimately matters?

05:21.090 --> 05:23.695
My father, Jesus is saying, showed you this.

05:23.795 --> 05:25.078
He's the one who revealed it.

05:25.098 --> 05:27.943
No matter what your earthly father was, my father is the one.

05:27.963 --> 05:32.752
And this is what I'm saying is God still lights things up for us.

05:32.892 --> 05:37.621
If we're willing to listen, if we're willing to pay attention, he reveals things to us.

05:37.641 --> 05:41.068
So if you go, there's this great interview online, Steven Spielberg.

05:41.188 --> 05:44.274
He's one of my favorite movie makers, directors.

05:44.770 --> 05:50.018
And he, of course, did this movie way back in the day called Close Encounters of the Third Kind, if you've never seen it.

05:50.038 --> 05:55.466
It's basically aliens come to Earth and the way aliens talk to people and communicate with people is through music.

05:55.526 --> 06:03.858
And so whatever we thought they were going to do, they show up and we thought, oh, they might talk to us in our language or they might blah, blah, blah, but there's this shared

06:03.938 --> 06:06.241
almost universal reality of music.

06:06.261 --> 06:08.003
And so they get up and they want to share.

06:08.023 --> 06:09.285
And so they play this keyboard.

06:09.325 --> 06:11.267
And it lights up.

06:11.287 --> 06:13.811
And so this is a computer and it lights up all these lights.

06:13.891 --> 06:16.013
And they communicate to human beings through music.

06:16.053 --> 06:17.936
And they're trying to say, hey, we're not here to kill everybody.

06:17.956 --> 06:20.099
And we're like, need, need, need, need, need, need.

06:20.119 --> 06:22.622
It's like this very famous John Williams score now.

06:22.982 --> 06:23.503
And so they do that.

06:24.164 --> 06:29.410
And years and years later, 20 years later, Steven Spielberg is in an interview with this guy named James Lipton.

06:29.450 --> 06:31.493
And Lipton looks at him and he says this.

06:31.553 --> 06:32.274
He says,

06:32.770 --> 06:46.672
You're in your movie, the aliens show up, and they decide to communicate through music that is communicated through a computer, through this electronic way, and Spielberg says yes.

06:47.053 --> 06:50.699
And he said, your parents were divorced, weren't they, when you were a kid?

06:50.719 --> 06:51.320
And he said, yeah.

06:51.941 --> 06:54.885
And he said, well, I did some research, and here's what I realized.

06:54.905 --> 07:00.274
Your mother was a musician, and your father was a computer scientist.

07:02.018 --> 07:05.121
And this story is you trying to bring them back together.

07:06.142 --> 07:14.131
And in that moment, you can go look at it up later, Spielberg literally sitting there with James Lipton is like, Oh my gosh, I have never realized this in my life.

07:14.832 --> 07:16.494
I literally sitting here right now.

07:17.154 --> 07:22.020
I have never realized that this whole story was about me trying to bring my parents back together.

07:22.440 --> 07:24.803
And he has this revelation, right?

07:24.823 --> 07:27.986
He has this moment where something was fuzzy to him.

07:28.514 --> 07:31.382
And now it's revealed, it's made clear.

07:31.423 --> 07:34.492
And this is what God is in the business of doing.

07:34.532 --> 07:37.561
The Lord is my light, right?

07:37.601 --> 07:42.034
Some of you hide in isolation and sin and pain and fear.

07:42.210 --> 07:44.353
and God's going, I want to bring you out into the light.

07:44.453 --> 07:51.262
Even me, I'm God and through the whole Old Testament, I spoke to you through the Bible and through prophets and Moses and all these people.

07:51.622 --> 08:02.877
But now in the New Testament, Jesus Christ shows up and he's the light and he kind of, he gets the fog away from any concept of who God is and he says, I'm God.

08:03.277 --> 08:05.821
I'm the one who's been speaking to you all along.

08:06.041 --> 08:07.763
I'm the God of the Old Testament.

08:07.883 --> 08:10.066
I'm the God who you need to come to know

08:10.562 --> 08:13.848
in order to have what he goes on to talk about is salvation.

08:13.868 --> 08:14.789
So this is what I love, man.

08:15.370 --> 08:17.815
Sometimes in life, a book hits different.

08:17.855 --> 08:20.099
You get into a song and it hits different.

08:20.119 --> 08:22.663
You look about the sunset and it hits different.

08:22.683 --> 08:26.390
And there's these moments in life where your soul seems to be cracking open.

08:26.430 --> 08:30.738
And that is God drawing you to himself and saying, Hey, I'm light.

08:31.339 --> 08:33.983
I want to draw you through the dark tunnel to the end of this tunnel.

08:34.204 --> 08:35.506
So he reveals

08:35.618 --> 08:36.199
this to us.

08:36.219 --> 08:37.881
He, he hunts us down.

08:37.901 --> 08:38.722
And let me just tell you something.

08:38.742 --> 08:40.404
He is still in the business of hunting down.

08:40.444 --> 08:43.168
If you are here today, he is speaking to you.

08:43.188 --> 08:45.631
If you're watching online, welcome to connect his church.

08:46.171 --> 08:50.637
He is speaking to you right now because he is light and he's not done talking.

08:51.338 --> 08:51.979
He's not done.

08:52.079 --> 08:55.123
Jesus says, my sheep can hear my voice.

08:56.244 --> 09:02.652
Can you do you ever hear him speak to you, challenge you, convict you, call you to something?

09:03.674 --> 09:03.954
So

09:04.578 --> 09:07.601
This past week, I'll give you an example of what happened to me.

09:08.322 --> 09:13.146
This past week, I was traveling down to this place called Forest Home, okay?

09:13.166 --> 09:14.948
They asked me to come and preach there.

09:15.449 --> 09:19.733
And so I go, I show up and I don't really realize it's in Southern California, up in the mountains, okay?

09:19.753 --> 09:21.795
It's up in the mountains of Southern California.

09:21.815 --> 09:29.783
They always say that, like all the guys who were there, they're like, hey, you know, you come up the mountain and you come up the mountain and then you're gonna go back down the mountain.

09:29.803 --> 09:33.106
And this was this, again, this men's retreat for a couple days, three days.

09:33.666 --> 09:42.699
I arrive and I go and my pastor had told me, my friend said, hey, listen, there's a really cool kind of Billy Graham thing there that you got to go check out.

09:42.739 --> 09:43.602
And I was like, OK.

09:43.810 --> 09:49.215
So I looked it up before I got there, and I showed up there, and I went and what it was.

09:49.536 --> 09:53.600
And it's 1949, Billy Graham was struggling with the concept of the Bible.

09:53.620 --> 10:02.709
He was a friend of Charles Templeton, who was this atheist, and he was casting doubts on all of the trust that Billy Graham had in the scriptures.

10:03.109 --> 10:04.250
And he's like, hey, it's not real.

10:04.270 --> 10:07.293
It's filled with all these miracle stories and silliness.

10:07.313 --> 10:07.934
You shouldn't believe it.

10:07.954 --> 10:11.858
So Billy Graham shows up at Forest Home Camp in 1949, kind of struggling.

10:12.354 --> 10:20.964
One day he's out for a walk and he's praying and thinking and he goes to this particular spot overlooking this valley And he puts his Bible on this tree stump.

10:21.025 --> 10:35.442
Okay, and he says God I don't understand everything that's in here But I'm gonna my faith is gonna transcend my doubts and for the rest of my life I'm gonna preach the Bible and he dedicates himself at forest home that day to preach the Bible and

10:35.554 --> 11:00.338
You know and trust it fully he puts on this tree stump and he says this is what I'm gonna give my life to and then he goes and he preaches that night and 400 people come to Christ and force home and he When he did it with more authority and conviction than anyone had ever seen and then he went on to start the 1949 Crusades in LA like a very short time after this moment and there was supposed to be three weeks it lasted eight weeks and

11:00.418 --> 11:07.585
And this was the beginning of the national prominence of Billy Graham and his ministry and him leading literally millions of people to Jesus.

11:08.726 --> 11:12.350
And so I went up there and I stood there at that spot.

11:12.390 --> 11:14.131
They have a rock there now dedicated to it.

11:14.151 --> 11:15.312
I'll show you a picture right here.

11:16.153 --> 11:25.022
That rock is overlooking the valley and that plaque says it's dedicated to Billy Graham in this place, this moment where he dedicated himself to follow the Bible and preach the Bible.

11:25.482 --> 11:29.266
Now here's the craziest thing about being up there preaching on that stage was

11:29.538 --> 11:38.894
The only reason I'm a Christian, and I think I've shared this story with you before, is because one day my grandfather was driving on his car and his engine broke down and he pulled into a random mechanic shop.

11:38.914 --> 11:46.066
This is like in 1950 or something, because my grandfather was 100 years old when he passed away a couple years ago.

11:46.626 --> 11:50.310
He pulls in a mechanic shop and the mechanic walks out and says, hey, I don't want your money.

11:50.510 --> 11:53.313
I want you to come down today with me to listen to this guy talk.

11:53.353 --> 11:56.777
And he brings him downtown, Maple Leaf Gardens, because I grew up in Toronto.

11:56.897 --> 11:59.240
And he watches Billy Graham.

11:59.260 --> 12:01.322
He'd never heard of him before, walk out and preach.

12:01.362 --> 12:02.503
And he gives his life to Jesus.

12:02.523 --> 12:04.185
And then he prayed for me my whole life.

12:04.786 --> 12:16.018
And so here I am at Forest Home Camp, where if I wouldn't be standing on that stage, I wouldn't be a Christian unless my grandfather had been saved by this guy who was at that camp and put his Bible on the stump,

12:16.098 --> 12:18.042
God loves to do full circles.

12:18.082 --> 12:23.174
And there I am preaching the same Bible, Billy Graham preached, preaching the same gospel that Billy Graham preached.

12:25.639 --> 12:29.829
And I'm going, God loves to still reveal.

12:29.849 --> 12:32.695
He loves to still speak.

12:32.715 --> 12:35.762
He loves to still blow the fog away.

12:36.034 --> 12:42.362
And in those moments, I feel reaffirmed in what I'm doing because I'm like, God, you got me here through all of these steps.

12:42.422 --> 12:46.327
And now here I am preaching to these people, the same Bible.

12:46.347 --> 12:48.470
You've done this amazing work.

12:49.271 --> 12:50.252
This is what God does.

12:50.313 --> 12:55.139
He doesn't leave us in the dark if we're willing to hear him, if we're willing to see him.

12:55.159 --> 12:57.562
He wants to be the light, right?

12:57.582 --> 13:03.730
He wants to shine and heal you and speak to you and still do miracles in your life and still do amazing things.

13:04.194 --> 13:07.220
He says he's the light, God is the light.

13:07.260 --> 13:11.489
And then he says he's the light and my salvation.

13:11.609 --> 13:13.212
Underline that, we're only on verse one.

13:13.273 --> 13:15.537
The Lord is my light and my salvation.

13:15.577 --> 13:17.361
Here's the beautiful thing about this word, salvation.

13:17.381 --> 13:19.826
It's one of the most important words of the whole Bible.

13:19.906 --> 13:21.627
God wants to save you, all right?

13:21.668 --> 13:23.469
You are lost, you're sinful.

13:23.789 --> 13:29.835
You need to come to know Jesus in order to be saved, to have the Holy Spirit, to get eternal life, to go to heaven when you die.

13:29.975 --> 13:30.996
All of those things are true.

13:31.016 --> 13:32.857
And he saves us.

13:32.957 --> 13:34.218
He's the only one who can save us.

13:34.699 --> 13:44.828
As we've talked about in this series, your money can't save you, your beauty can't save you, your success can't save you, your grandmother's faith can't save you, your marriage can't save you.

13:44.848 --> 13:49.892
Because one day, as Timothy Keller talks about, you're gonna bury your spouse and if you're spouse,

13:49.872 --> 13:57.023
If you're having a great marriage is your functional savior, if it's the way you feel, all the joy that you feel, then you're going to bury it one day.

13:57.083 --> 14:04.214
If your job is the only way that you feel happiness and joy and contentment in life, then one day you're going to lose it.

14:04.254 --> 14:07.700
And if you lose it, all of your salvation goes away.

14:08.181 --> 14:09.523
And so it's very important.

14:09.983 --> 14:14.290
And I love this, the word salvation in the Hebrew, it means this, to be broad,

14:14.402 --> 14:17.045
to be spacious to enlarge.

14:17.145 --> 14:17.546
I love this.

14:17.606 --> 14:23.212
It's like deliverance from being compressed and confined and cramped.

14:23.232 --> 14:25.015
Don't we all want that, right?

14:25.675 --> 14:32.784
We want the concept of the idea that God is gonna take from where you are right now and enlarge you, right?

14:32.824 --> 14:41.394
Enlarge your life, enlarge your impact, enlarge your joy, enlarge your satisfaction, enlarge your contentment in life, enlarge

14:41.570 --> 14:47.620
who you are that now you are someone who's living an eternal life and eternal life in the Bible.

14:48.801 --> 14:54.831
It doesn't just mean like a span of time, right, that you're going to now live forever because everyone's going to live forever.

14:54.851 --> 15:01.682
It actually means a quality of time that you're now living God's heavenly life in the present time.

15:01.722 --> 15:04.306
And I was a very different person.

15:04.386 --> 15:09.130
I can tell you, this is what he's saying, I wanna enlarge you, I wanna take you away from your confines.

15:09.170 --> 15:16.997
The things I was confined to before I came to know Jesus, the drugs and the partying and all the stuff, some of you are needing that.

15:17.057 --> 15:23.062
You're stuck in these addictions or these habits or these lifestyles or whatever, and you're needing God to enlarge you.

15:23.102 --> 15:34.372
It doesn't just mean this word salvation in Hebrew, it doesn't mean you're gonna go to heaven when you die, it means that, but it means right now in the present enlarging you from the confines of the things that have you in bondage.

15:34.352 --> 15:36.514
And it was fascinating the other day.

15:36.554 --> 15:39.858
I was listening to this, um, this communicator.

15:39.898 --> 15:43.702
He made a comment that I never really thought of before and I've been a pastor for a long time.

15:44.523 --> 15:47.766
He said he's done a lot of demonic deliverance ministry in his life.

15:47.786 --> 15:54.153
And that's not something I do a lot of, but I really believe in it because I see people who are oppressed by the demonic and evil things in their life.

15:54.573 --> 15:55.354
And he said, you know what?

15:55.374 --> 16:03.282
The number one thing that people are demonized by in their life, the number one thing that keeps people oppressed is unforgiveness.

16:04.130 --> 16:16.128
He said, there are things in people's lives, things that people have done to people where they can't get free of the bondage of unforgiveness and evil literally keeps them in bondage.

16:16.149 --> 16:20.655
And this is the kind of thing that some of you there, right now you need to be going, who are the people I need to forgive?

16:20.696 --> 16:22.058
Who are the people I need to let?

16:22.078 --> 16:23.440
This is what salvation means.

16:23.460 --> 16:25.503
He wants to enlarge your life.

16:25.763 --> 16:28.568
And the thing is, we need saving, right?

16:28.628 --> 16:30.130
We think that

16:30.722 --> 16:33.365
The only way we can cause this is modern psychology, right?

16:33.385 --> 16:41.636
Carl Jung said, the only way you can reach self actualization is when you realize that you're great and you're wonderful and you got to go inside yourself.

16:41.656 --> 16:43.238
And this is what we tell in our modern thing.

16:43.658 --> 16:51.448
But the Bible says, no, the only way you ever be saved or come to self realization is to realize that you're sinful, that you are a potential monster, right?

16:51.488 --> 16:54.872
That you are constantly trying to fool the world.

16:54.892 --> 16:55.573
You're sinful.

16:55.613 --> 16:56.154
You're a mess.

16:56.174 --> 16:59.538
The people around you don't even know the things you think about.

17:00.066 --> 17:00.732
in the dark.

17:01.984 --> 17:02.994
You need saving.

17:04.322 --> 17:13.916
I always look for opportunities where God is trying to remind me of the humility that I need to realize that I need him every day to be my salvation.

17:13.936 --> 17:16.340
I went to the Apple Store recently and I was returning my phone.

17:16.380 --> 17:17.342
I'm like, this phone doesn't work.

17:17.882 --> 17:21.027
The guy behind the camera is like, well, it doesn't work then and sorry.

17:21.247 --> 17:23.090
And I said, no, no, I need a new phone.

17:23.130 --> 17:24.552
No, it's not covered.

17:24.813 --> 17:25.354
I'm like, come on.

17:25.574 --> 17:26.916
And I start into an argument with him.

17:26.936 --> 17:28.138
And he brings it back from the back.

17:28.158 --> 17:29.280
He's like, sorry, it can't be fixed.

17:29.320 --> 17:30.782
I'm like, what are you talking about?

17:30.802 --> 17:31.743
I want to talk to your manager.

17:31.763 --> 17:33.586
I want to talk to your manager.

17:34.114 --> 17:39.672
And then all of a sudden after like five minutes of this, he looks at me and goes, I'm sorry Pastor Mark, I can't help you.

17:39.712 --> 17:42.741
And I'm like, wait, will you know who I am?

17:42.802 --> 17:45.490
Why didn't you lead with that?

17:45.698 --> 17:49.845
Right, if you would have led with you know who I am, I would have been the nicest guy on the planet.

17:49.865 --> 17:52.389
I would have been like, oh my goodness, you know, phones.

17:52.910 --> 17:54.152
Who cares about phones?

17:54.252 --> 17:55.874
I mean, this is like worldly possessions.

17:55.914 --> 17:56.615
You can have it.

17:56.816 --> 17:57.998
All right, you can have all my money.

17:58.038 --> 17:59.380
I'm such a good righteous person.

18:00.221 --> 18:07.513
He would have told me, but he waited 10 minutes of me yelling and screaming and being a complete depraved idiot before he goes, oh, by the way, I know who you are.

18:08.314 --> 18:11.239
See, here's the thing, I'm always trying to fool the world, right?

18:11.259 --> 18:13.202
Because I'm just like you, I'm sinful.

18:14.050 --> 18:16.539
I want to project something out into the world that I'm not.

18:17.241 --> 18:17.924
And here's the thing.

18:18.967 --> 18:21.757
God wants to not only be the light of your life.

18:22.099 --> 18:23.584
Look at verse one, man, hold on to this.

18:23.624 --> 18:25.330
He wants to be your salvation.

18:25.762 --> 18:30.247
He wants to save you and some of you, you're sitting here and you need saving.

18:30.387 --> 18:34.351
You need to realize that you're sinful and you need to repent and give your life to Jesus.

18:34.391 --> 18:41.899
You need to turn from the things in your life and say, I treasure and love and trust the death and resurrection of Jesus on my behalf.

18:41.919 --> 18:42.740
