21:07.891 --> 21:13.778
And if she's someone who's given her life to Jesus, we're gonna do a baptism tomorrow in the pool.

21:13.986 --> 21:15.589
in Palm Springs, right over.

21:15.609 --> 21:16.571
Look at this golf course.

21:16.611 --> 21:18.635
We're going to do this even with one person.

21:19.376 --> 21:20.558
And the whole family's like buzzing.

21:20.578 --> 21:21.179
They're like, wait, what?

21:21.841 --> 21:22.462
Are you serious?

21:22.562 --> 21:23.283
I don't.

21:23.303 --> 21:26.229
And so the next morning, woke up, went in the backyard and I said, tell me your story.

21:26.249 --> 21:28.133
And she said, she grew up in China.

21:28.173 --> 21:32.461
And years ago, she, she got this little like cut in her eyeball.

21:32.501 --> 21:35.045
And it was like this white thing that was going through her eyeball.

21:35.106 --> 21:37.490
And she went to the optometrist and they said, you might

21:37.666 --> 21:39.168
go blind in your left eye.

21:39.188 --> 21:41.310
And of course, she started crying as she was overwhelmed.

21:41.851 --> 21:43.953
She was with her real turn, her grandma.

21:43.973 --> 21:46.076
And she said, the only thing we can do is go to a church.

21:46.496 --> 21:50.701
And so she showed up to the first church she could find because she's like, I need Jesus to heal me.

21:50.741 --> 21:57.148
If Jesus is real, and so she stayed for all the services and just prayed and cried, Jesus, please heal me, please heal me.

21:57.168 --> 22:02.654
And she said, the next morning, Mark, no joke, the next morning I woke up and my eye was completely healed.

22:03.495 --> 22:05.778
And she's like, this is the God I want to follow.

22:05.954 --> 22:12.951
And so she started exporting Christianity and then she came into this family that I was visiting and they read the Bible every night and they'd say the Lord's prayer.

22:13.251 --> 22:17.862
And she's like, and this started welling up in me this desire to know this God named Jesus.

22:18.203 --> 22:21.170
And I said, so do you want to come to know him right now and literally?

22:21.378 --> 22:27.227
This is four days ago, we're sitting in his backyard at nine o'clock in the morning and I lead her to Christ.

22:27.247 --> 22:28.609
She literally repents her sin.

22:28.869 --> 22:31.413
She praised the prayer to receive Christ into her life.

22:31.834 --> 22:43.031
And 15 minutes later, we're down in the waters of the pool and I'm baptizing her in front of this whole family as they're applauding and crying and watching this girl step into the life that God has for her.

22:43.812 --> 22:47.578
And her boyfriend looked at me and I said, it's her faith legitimate like this.

22:47.598 --> 22:50.322
And he says, Mark, I think this is why you were here.

22:51.170 --> 22:52.664
See, this is the thing, guys.

22:53.250 --> 22:55.794
God speaks and you gotta listen.

22:56.418 --> 23:01.406
Of course it was a bit of a mess because I had to rearrange a whole bunch of meetings because I never came back on Sunday.

23:01.426 --> 23:03.649
I came back on Tuesday and it was all family stuff.

23:03.669 --> 23:06.654
I had to be reorganized but God was trying to save.

23:06.714 --> 23:08.236
And this is what he does.

23:08.276 --> 23:18.011
He's not only the light, he has the salvation and he's speaking and he's moving and he's drawing men and women and kids and teenagers to himself in droves.

23:18.051 --> 23:20.155
And as you're watching this right now, think about it.

23:20.175 --> 23:22.418
If you're sitting in church, why are you here?

23:22.690 --> 23:27.175
Yes, you might come here as a routine, but he's trying to speak to you and do something in your life.

23:27.235 --> 23:30.519
And maybe some of you, you are here because you're exploring Christianity.

23:30.539 --> 23:31.980
It's time to be saved.

23:32.881 --> 23:38.027
It's time to say I've seen the light in Jesus and I wanna give my life to Jesus, just like Catherine did.

23:38.047 --> 23:45.876
This is a picture of Catherine that day we got that I baptized her in the morning and standing in front of the pool just after her baptism as her whole family is there applauding.

23:45.916 --> 23:47.858
It's a beautiful thing.

23:48.866 --> 23:50.168
This is what God is trying to do.

23:50.248 --> 23:52.833
And then I love this because look at what salvation does.

23:53.093 --> 23:56.379
It filters down to the very practical things in our life.

23:56.419 --> 23:59.785
Look at the rest of verse one, whom shall I fear?

24:01.448 --> 24:06.376
See if all of what I just said is true, then fear dies.

24:06.416 --> 24:14.450
If all of what I just said is true, then the anxiety of your life can go away and it can be like, I have God.

24:14.722 --> 24:16.464
Because we do have fears in life.

24:16.564 --> 24:17.766
Constant fears in life.

24:17.806 --> 24:19.668
We fear dying.

24:19.748 --> 24:22.751
Dying is one of the great fears of all of us.

24:22.812 --> 24:25.615
It's what philosophy was birthed out of.

24:25.715 --> 24:29.860
What do I do with this existential question of death?

24:30.501 --> 24:33.524
Everything we do in life is a defense against death.

24:33.905 --> 24:38.450
I was walking through a mall in Phoenix years ago with Aaron, I remember.

24:38.594 --> 24:49.348
or walking through, and this guy came out of nowhere, and he grabbed this lady's purse, who was like five feet from us, grabs her purse, and he just takes off through the mall, just running through the mall, and she's screaming, and she's like, help me!

24:49.828 --> 24:50.309
Help me!

24:50.329 --> 24:51.290
He's got my purse!

24:52.151 --> 24:59.320
And I was like, you know, growing up as a kid, you always kind of wondered, I did, I was like, I wonder what would happen, I wonder what I would do, all right?

24:59.440 --> 25:07.250
Because I see myself as like a star, I wonder what I would do if someone ever did that, like grab someone's purse and took off through the mall, I wonder what I would do.

25:07.330 --> 25:10.814
Well, it turns out I would do nothing.

25:13.357 --> 25:14.839
I would do absolutely nothing.

25:14.859 --> 25:18.423
In fact, I grabbed Aaron and we ran the other way because I didn't want to die.

25:18.523 --> 25:19.243
You never know.

25:19.264 --> 25:20.265
I don't want to.

25:20.285 --> 25:26.131
This drives our whole life as fear, fear of not being liked, fear of failure, fear of not being successful.

25:26.652 --> 25:35.602
And God goes, man, once you've given your life to me, I know you have fears in your marriage, fears with raising your kids, fears with money, fears with friendships, fears with sickness.

25:36.418 --> 25:41.664
God is more than just light and just salvation.

25:41.704 --> 25:43.766
He's also the one because those two things are true.

25:45.168 --> 25:48.552
He lights up your life in a way that takes away your fears.

25:48.792 --> 25:53.337
You're sitting there at three o'clock in the morning and all the fears start to overwhelm you.

25:53.818 --> 25:54.438
He's my light.

25:54.458 --> 25:55.420
He's my salvation.

25:55.440 --> 25:58.363
And I don't have to be scared anymore.

25:59.304 --> 25:59.684
Right?

25:59.885 --> 26:00.365
I don't have to.

26:00.445 --> 26:01.386
I don't have to do that.

26:02.888 --> 26:03.989
I read this quote this week.

26:04.009 --> 26:04.690
It was great.

26:05.282 --> 26:07.626
