28:29.003 --> 28:31.506
Like Jesus grits his teeth and he's like,

28:31.618 --> 28:32.099
fine.

28:32.439 --> 28:34.122
Mark, you were just here 20 minutes ago.

28:34.182 --> 28:35.784
What do you need my blood again for?

28:36.145 --> 28:36.365
Here.

28:37.006 --> 28:39.089
And that's how we tend to think about Jesus.

28:39.109 --> 28:44.458
He reluctantly gives us the accomplishment of the cross when we need it because we're sinful.

28:44.478 --> 28:50.367
And Dane Orlin, working on the theology of a guy named Thomas Goodwin says, no, no, no, no.

28:51.428 --> 28:52.129
Picture this.

28:52.210 --> 28:55.154
Picture you are a doctor who works

28:55.458 --> 28:56.423
tirelessly.

28:56.443 --> 29:04.242
You spend all your time, all your money, decades of your life developing a vaccine to help a group of people in some jungle in South

29:04.354 --> 29:05.616
America somewhere, okay?

29:05.636 --> 29:07.278
Now, don't get distracted by the vaccine.

29:07.538 --> 29:08.339
All right, comment, all right.

29:08.379 --> 29:11.723
Some of you are like, yeah, vaccines, that's not the point of the story.

29:12.144 --> 29:24.599
All right, so picture yourself, you developed a vaccine and you go into the jungle and you go to, now imagine these people are in the jungle and they start coming out in droves in order to use the vaccine to heal themselves.

29:24.619 --> 29:26.801
Would you be reluctant and angry?

29:27.102 --> 29:30.546
No, you would be, it would bring you great joy.

29:30.786 --> 29:35.553
for you to apply your hard work to their life because they need it.

29:36.295 --> 29:42.324
And he says, listen, Jesus isn't applying his death to you reluctantly and gritting his teeth.

29:43.025 --> 29:44.547
It gives him great joy.

29:44.587 --> 29:46.811
This is why he came.

29:46.871 --> 29:52.800
This is why he wakes up in the morning that he looks at you and he says, it gives me great joy to forgive you.

29:53.401 --> 29:55.845
Some of you, that's the thing you needed to hear today.

29:56.105 --> 29:57.267
That's the thing you need to hear.

29:57.668 --> 29:59.090
It gives him great joy.

30:00.546 --> 30:01.327
to forgive you.

30:01.888 --> 30:07.756
For the joy set before him, the book of Hebrews says, Jesus Christ endured the cross.

30:08.637 --> 30:20.193
For the joy set before him, he endured the cross, the joy that he was going to experience in the cross and the resurrection and the ascension and sitting at the right hand of God and going back to glory.

30:20.213 --> 30:24.959
But the joy that all of that accomplished for you is a beautiful thing.

30:25.019 --> 30:26.962
And so do you

30:27.202 --> 30:28.348
Do you believe in it?

30:28.408 --> 30:31.102
Do you treasure it above all things?

30:31.223 --> 30:34.098
Do you hold your whole life?

30:34.210 --> 30:37.333
and say, Jesus, I'm gonna let you be my light and my salvation.

30:37.373 --> 30:45.723
And then the last verse I wanna hit, and you could go through this entire beautiful Psalm, and it does talk about to gaze on the beauty of the Lord, verse four, right?

30:46.123 --> 30:49.126
I wanna dwell in the house of the Lord forever, all the days of my life.

30:49.487 --> 30:50.668
I wanna gaze on his beauty.

30:50.688 --> 30:54.993
Do you find, as we talked about in another sermon in this series, do you see Jesus as a treasure?

30:55.013 --> 30:57.415
Do you see him as beautiful, not just helpful, useful?

30:57.736 --> 31:03.442
Do you see him as the one that, where he's the most amazing thing in your life?

31:04.162 --> 31:06.806
And then verse 13 says, I remain confident of this.

31:07.427 --> 31:11.233
I will see the goodness of the Lord in the land of the living.

31:11.253 --> 31:14.077
I will see the goodness of the Lord in the land of the living.

31:14.117 --> 31:18.484
I will see the goodness of God, not just that He's right and true, but that He's good.

31:18.764 --> 31:21.989
And I'll do it now in the land of the living.

31:22.270 --> 31:24.253
So two things to share with you.

31:25.014 --> 31:25.875
And then I'll pray for you.

31:26.116 --> 31:32.786
There is this writer right now and he just, he wrote this book and he talks about what different generations are asking.

31:33.346 --> 31:46.946
Okay, so he says that boomers, if you're a boomer in the audience, they ask the question, is this thing that I'm listening to, being exposed to, is it true, right?

